name: Small Vintage apartment near Old Quebec
description:
Completely renovated in the last year "Vintage style" with pronounced touches of wood.

It is a few minutes walk from all that is wonderful in old Quebec! If you come for work, the apartment is a 4-minute walk from the Center des Congrès de Québec.

The apartment contains everything you need for cooking as well as high-speed WIFI and an HD TV.
neighborhood_overview:
In the heart of Old Quebec, this is the most lively place in Quebec City.
- Eat at renowned high-end restaurants, or have small cartier pubs with renowned microbrewery beers.
Walk to Château Frontenac, in the small lanes that make Old Quebec famous, or on Rue St-Jean, which is one of the main streets.
- You can go around the wonderful Plains of Abraham.

And all this, a few minutes walk from the apartment!

name: Residence on "Place Royale"
description:
Live the "royale" experience!
(CITQ 301382)

The apartment, taking up the entire 2nd floor of a restored 19th century building with acces to Place Royale (1608), will throw you in Québec's history, its unique architecture plus the restaurants, terraces, boutiques, antiques shops and museums around... Just a few steps from the majestic St-Lawrence river!
neighborhood_overview:
"Place Royale" historical district, cradle of New France in North America has celebrated in july 2008 its 400th anniversary. You'll literally walk in Samuel de Champlain's footsteps, founder of Quebec city in 1608!

All around, the restaurants and art galleries of "petit Champlain", St-Paul & Sault-au-Matelot streets, Québec-Levis ferry and the Museum of Civilization will be your first discoveries.

Then up the funicular you'll access to Frontenac Castle and all the marvels of upper town!

name: Magnifique maison de ville dans le Vieux-Québec!
description: Our townhouse is perfect for a group of friends, family or workers. Conveniently located, you will be within minutes walking of the most wonderful attractions of Old Quebec. The famous Château Frontenac, the festive Rue Saint-Jean, the Plains of Abraham, the turbulent Grande Allée and much more.
neighborhood_overview:
Quebec City is divided into three main areas:
Downtown, commonly called "la Basse-Ville": When you stay in this area, you need to go up to the Haute-Ville.
Upper Town includes Old Quebec and Le Faubourg St-Jean-Baptiste:
Old Quebec with its old fortifications. This is the neighborhood everyone will visit. Formerly, the fortifications were used to protect themselves from the English, now it's to keep tourists inside;) In short, this area is superb, you'll love it. It is mainly for tourism. You can buy an "I LOVE QUÉBEC" t-shirt and other souvenirs in the many shops there.
The Faubourg Saint-Jean-Baptiste is next to the fortifications. And this is where my property is located. Here, you'll live with the locals. Rue Saint-Jean is a beautiful shopping street where you can walk and enjoy the lively atmosphere. This street will take you straight into the fortifications, a 5-minute walk from your home.
